    • Constructor Detail

      • EquestriaMap

        public EquestriaMap()
        Creates a canvas displaying the map of Equestria overlaid with its coordinate system. Origin of the map (0, 0) is in the top-left corner, horizontal (X) range is [0-37], vertical (Y) range is [0-27].
        See Also:
        DrawingFactory.open(), plot(int, int), line(int, int, int, int), lineTo(int, int), circle(int, int, int)

      • lineTo

        public boolean lineTo(int x,
                      int y)
        Draws a line from the last position drawn on the map to the given coordinate. i.e.: if last draw operation was line(10, 10, 20, 20), the line drawn by line(42, 64) has the starting point at (20, 20) and the ending point at (42, 64)
        Parameters:
        x - - x coordinate of the ending point of the line
        y - - y coordinate of the ending point of the line
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise
        See Also:
        line(int, int, int, int)

      • circle

        public boolean circle(int xCenter,
                      int yCenter,
                      int radius)
        Draws a circle with the given center and of the given diameter. If the circle is not fully contained on the map, the method will not fail, but only the portions that intersect the map area will be shown. The center of the circle is also drawn on the map as if it was drawn by plot().
        Parameters:
        xCenter - - x coordinate of the center of the circle.
        yCenter - - y coordinate of the center of the circle.
        radius - - the radius of the circle
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise
        See Also:
        plot(int, int)
